This paper deals with generating synthetic images for handwritten text recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of data augmentation techniques, which is a common practice in natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR) tasks (cs.IR). The generated data could be useful for improving the performance of handwritten word spotting and recognition tasks, which are also part of the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of deep network architectures, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
